Underline: \underline{...}You can have multiple images in one figure (e.g. side-by-side).<br><a rel="noopener nofollow" class="external-link is-unresolved" href="https://www.overleaf.com/project/68c07400736bbed0e4331fdd" target="_self">https://www.overleaf.com/project/68c07400736bbed0e4331fdd</a>LaTeX provides two writing modes for typesetting mathematics:
inline math mode used for writing formulas that are part of a paragraph.
display math mode used to write expressions that are not part of a text or paragraph and are typeset on separate lines.
